    <item>
      <title>Decoding ubiquitin chain signals in physiologic and stressed states</title>
      <link>https://samantlab.github.io/current-research/ubiquitin-altpqc/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 09 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://samantlab.github.io/current-research/ubiquitin-altpqc/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Although Lys48-linked ubiquitin is the canonical signal for protein clearance by the proteasome, &amp;lsquo;alternative&amp;rsquo; ubiquitin signals play critical yet poorly-characterised roles in misfolded protein clearance&amp;mdash;especially under acute stress.
Using linkage-specific ubiquitin probes and perturbation tools, we are uncovering how these additional ubiquitin signalling events maintain proteome robustness in a range of physiologic and stressed cellular contexts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current projects on ubiquitin signalling include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;impact-of-specific-ubiquitin-linkages-in-misfolded-protein-clearance&#34;&gt;Impact of specific ubiquitin linkages in misfolded protein clearance&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Leads: &lt;a href=&#34;https://samantlab.github.io/author/harvey-johnston&#34;&gt;Harvey Johnston&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=&#34;https://samantlab.github.io/author/richard-odle&#34;&gt;Richard Odle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborators: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.kulathulab.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Yogesh Kulathu&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.imb.de/research/ulrich/research&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Helle Ulrich&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ceb-mng.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Gabriele Kaminski-Schierle&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ppu.mrc.ac.uk/research/principal-investigator/kirby-swatek&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Kirby Swatek&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
